info.name: BGL API
info.description: The BGL API is an easy and secure way  for users to grant access to BGL data to third-party applications without sharing a username and password.

item.name: Getting Started
Staging (Sandbox)
item.description:
Our staging environment (https://api.staging.bgl360.com.au) is used to test your application and integration with BGL's products

 1. Please email api@bglcorp.com.au to get access to our Staging environment.  
 2. Explore our documentation below to see what each endpoint does
 3. If you get stuck or require your API scope to upgraded please contact api@bglcorp.com.au

item.name: Production Environment
item.description:
Our production environment (https://api.bgl360.com.au) is used to access BGL's client's data for Simple Fund 360 and CAS 360. To get access to our Production Environment you must have done the following: 

1. Developed and tested your integration on our staging environment
2. Email api@bglcorp.com.au to get access to receive Production environment credentials.  
2. You must agree to [BGL's Terms and Conditions](https://api.bgl360.com.au/home/termsAndConditions) and sign our [BGL API agreement](https://blog.api.bgl360.com.au/assets/Files/BGLStandardAPIAgreement.docx) to get access to our Production Environment
3. To upgrade your scope on BGL's production environment 
* must demonstrate your integration to BGL to get access to BGL's Production Environment.
* you must complete [BGL's security questionnaire ](https://www.formpl.us/form/1340596004)


Once all these steps have been completed you will receive the following:

1. Authentication details for BGL's Production API
2. For commercial products, an opportunity for your integration details, to be placed on our Help website. 
3. For commercial products an opportunity to speak to our Marketing department about Joint Marketing,Emails, podcasts, webinars etc

item.name: Authorization (OAuth2)
Prerequisites
item.description:
In order to consume the BGL API:

**1. Register a BGL Application**
You need to register your API application with BGL first. See [Add Application](https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/1087993/SVYjVNnn?version=latest#9776acf7-4623-436a-b3c8-feb5cdcd825f)

You will either need to login using your BGL Credentials. If you do not have a BGL Account BGL can create a demo account for you. 

The consuming application can be registered with BGL by using My Application section.

2.**Certificate Policy**

Ensure the Amazon Root CA Certificate bundles should be installed in your applications/operating systems.

Certificates provided by Amazon Certificate Manager are verified by Amazon’s certificate authority (CA). Any browser, application, or OS that includes the Amazon Root CA 1, Starfield Services Root Certificate Authority - G2, or Starfield Class 2 Certification Authority trusts certificates provided by ACM.

Link to access CA Certs issued by Amazon: https://www.amazontrust.com/repository/

item.name: Authorization Code Grant

query.description: [**REQUIRED**] the value of this should always be: authorization_code
[*Optional*] An opaque value, used for security purposes. If this request parameter is set in the request, then it is returned to the application as part of the redirect_uri.
[**REQUIRED**]
[**REQUIRED**] Must be scope registered to your application.
[**REQUIRED**] Must be a URL registred to you application. A successful response from this endpoint results in a redirect to this URL.

request.description: The authorization code is a temporary code that the client will exchange for an access token. The code itself is obtained from the authorization server where the user gets a chance to see what the information the client is requesting, and approve or deny the request.

query.description:
[**REQUIRED**] the value of this should always be: authorization_code for initial authorization
to refresh the token, the value of this should always be: refresh_token
[**REQUIRED**] The Authorization Code obtained from the BGL API. This is not required to Refresh an Access Token
[**REQUIRED**] Must be a scope registred to your application. Currently available scopes are listed in the API Scopes.

[**REQUIRED**] The URI that will be used to redirect after authorisation. This value must match one of the defined OAuth 2.0 Redirect URLs in your application configuration. See Obtaining BGL API Credentials on how to set redirect uri.

request.description:
Once the client application has the Authorization code, then the client application can obtain an Access Token. The Access Token will contain vital information that is required to access the BGL API.

In order for the client to obtain an Access Token, the client application should send a request to the BGL API as follows.

item.description: The authorization code is a temporary code that the client will exchange for an access token. The code itself is obtained from the authorization server where the user gets a chance to see what the information the client is requesting, and approve or deny the request. The Access Token's purpose is to inform the API that the bearer of the token has been authorized to access the API and perform a predetermined set of actions (which is specified by the scopes granted). ## Step 1. Initiate request Your app/website initiates the flow by directing the user to the **Authorize URL** . The URL can put inserted into an `` tag or attached to a button. Example: ```javascript Connect Your BGL Account ``` Connect Your BGL Account ## Step 2. The user approves the request Upon being directed to the BGL auth server, the user sees the authorization request shown in the illustration below. **2.1 Login page** If the user has not logged in to any BGL system prior to requesting an Authorization Code, the user will be redirected to the BGL Login Page. The user needs to input a username and password and select Sign In. ![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/login.png) **2.2 Authorization Page** The Authorization Page will show what access you will have to their accounts. If the user has not previously accepted the application's permission request, the grant has expired or been manually revoked by the user, the system will be redirected to the API's authorisation screen as displayed below. Tas shown below. *Switch Firm* If the user has accees to multiple Firms (Businesses), this screen also allows you to switch firm if required by clicking on the Switch Firm button. You will be redirected to the Please choose a firm page where you can select a different firm from the drop-down list. **Choose Firm** If access has already been granted to fund(s) for the selected firm, the number of funds will be displayed on-screen. If you are performing Authorisation for the first time the count displays the total number of funds avialable for the given firm. Please see Fund Selection on changing the accessible funds. ## Step 3. API redirects the user back to your app/website. The service sends a redirect header redirecting the user’s browser back to the app that made the request. The redirect will include a “code” in the URL (and the original “state” if used). https://exampleapp.com/bglcallback?code=Yzk5ZDczMzRlNDEwY&state=5ca75bd30 ## Step 4. You exchange the auth code for an access token The app uses the auth code to get an access token by making a POST request to the authorization server. You will need to pass Basic Authorization header for authorization. curl -i -X POST \ -H "Accept:application/json" \ 'https://api.staging.bgl360.com.au/oauth/token?grant_type=authorization_code&code=xxxxxx&scope=audit&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fexampleapp.com%2Fbglcallback' The authorization server will validate the request and respond with an access token and optional refresh token if the access token will expire. Response: { access_token: "df2f0e40-606f-4311-8066-590732fd126b" token_type: "bearer" refresh_token: "c50a429f-9a6d-449d-8d82-4899998fe27b" expires_in: 581977 scope: “audit” }

item.name: Refresh Token

query.description: [**REQUIRED**] to refresh the token, the value of this should always be: refresh_token
[**REQUIRED**] A URL-encoded, space-delimited list of member permissions your application is requesting on behalf of the user. Currently available scopes are listed in the API Scopes.

[**REQUIRED**] The URI that will be used to redirect after authorisation. This value must match one of the defined OAuth 2.0 Redirect URLs in your application configuration. See Obtaining BGL API Credentials on how to set redirect uri.
[**REQUIRED**] Refresh Token obtained previously. This field is mandatory if grant_type = refresh_token

request.description: A refresh token allows an application to obtain a new access token without prompting the user.

query.description:
the value of this should always be: authorization_code for initial authorization
to refresh the token, the value of this should always be: refresh_token

The URI that will be used to redirect after authorisation. This value must match one of the defined OAuth 2.0 Redirect URLs in your application configuration, as described in the Oauth2 Documentation. See Obtaining BGL API Credentials on how to set redirect uri.
Refresh Token obtained previously. This field is mandatory if grant_type = refresh_token

header.value: Bearer realm="oauth", error="invalid_token", error_description="Invalid access token: f62aed08-8ef8-429f-b0f5-b418c238de4f"

item.description:
The Refresh Token grant type is used by API clients to exchange a refresh token for an access token when the access token has expired or about to expire. This allows clients to continue to have a valid access token without further interaction with the user.

The grant_type parameter must be set to “refresh_token”.

BGL checks whether the refresh token is valid, and has not expired.
If everything checks out, the service can generate an access token and issue a new refresh token in the response.

**What is Oauth 2.0?**

OAuth 2.0 is the industry standard developed by IETF for providing client applications with “secure delegated access”. 

If you are new to using OAuth 2.0 please see [BGL's OAuth2 Guide](https://blog.api.bgl360.com.au/oauth2-guide/). This includes a step by step process of how to test using Postman.

item.name: Security
item.description:
Apps connecting to BGL's API must meet these requirements: 

## Encryption key management
Please ensure that your app meets these requirements for OAuth token management: 

 - OAuth tokens or customer-identifying information must not be exposed within your app or shared with other parties. 
 - Encrypt and store the refresh token in persistent memory. 
 - Encrypt the refresh token with a symmetric algorithm (3DES or AES). AES-128 or greater is preferred. 
 - Store your AES key in your app, in a separate configuration file.

## Encryption in transit
SSL must be configured to support only TLS version 1.2 or higher. 
- BGL does not support 1.1 or lower. 
- TLS version 1.2 using AES 256 or higher with SHA-256 is recommended.


## SSO Certificates
Please include the Amazon Root CA to your CA Certificate bundle for your application/OS.
Certificates provided by Amazon Certificate Manager are verified by Amazon’s certificate authority (CA). Any browser, application, or OS that includes the Amazon Root CA 1, Starfield Services Root Certificate Authority - G2, or Starfield Class 2 Certification Authority trusts certificates provided by ACM.
To access CA Certs issued by Amazon, refer to the following webpage:
https://www.amazontrust.com/repository/

item.name: Add My Application
item.description:
This section explains how an Organisation or a User can register to receive access to the BGL 360 API.

Before you can use My Application, you will need a BGL Product (Simple Fund 360 or CAS 360) username and password.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/addApplication.png)

1. Go to the [API website (Production)](https://api.bgl360.com.au) or [API website (Staging)](https://api.staging.bgl360.com.au)and select DEVELOPER from the main menu. 

2. Input your the BGL Product Username and Password. 

Alternatively,you can access the API Management by navigating to the BGL API application on the App Switcher in either Simple Fund 360 or CAS 360.  
![](https://sf360.zendesk.com/hc/article_attachments/360028553531/image2018-3-5_11_32_5.png)

## Add Application
1. Select **Add Application** on the Application List page. This will redirect the user to the 'Setup New Application' Page
2. Following are the details that needs to be added to create an API Application/Client.


| Field | Description | Required |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| Name     | your API Application/Client Name.     | Yes     |
| Redirect URLs    | The URL that will be used to redirect after Authorisation. The first URL entered in the list will be used as the Default Redirect URL (which will be displayed in a different colour in the list). However, if you wish to use any other Redirect URL in the list that you have added, then you will need to provide this in the Request for Authorisation Code. At least one Redirect URL should be added to this field. You can add upto 5 Redicrect URLs. Only valid URLs can be entered into this field.  We restrict localhost as it causes our API to loop back to itself. You can use IPv4 localhost address such as http://127.0.0.1:80 or a URL redirection such as https://goo.gl/vRtUkM | Yes     |
| Scope     | The API Application/Client Scope. Please see API Scopes for more details. Currently the supported type is 'Developer'.      | Yes     |

3. Once you have entered the necessary information, ensure you have read and agreed to the the Terms and Conditions

## Why can't I enter Local Host as a redirect URL ? 
We restrict localhost as it causes our API to loop back to itself. You can use IPv4 localhost address such as http://127.0.0.1:80 or a URL redirection such as https://goo.gl/vRtUkM
## Do I need to create more than one application?
In most cases you will oncly need one application. One application can access unlimited user accounts from unlimited firms.

item.name: Edit Application
item.description:
The Edit Application Details page, as displayed below, allows you to make changes to the application information you have previously entered.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/editApplication.png)



| Field | Description | Required |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| Name     | The API Application/Client Name.    | Yes     |
| Owner     | Username who owns/created the application. This is a read-only field.    | Yes     |
| Website     | The Web Site URL of the Organization using this Application/Client. The entered URL should be a valid, well formed URL.    | No     |
| Logo in Authorization Page   | The Logo that will be displayed in the Authorization Page. Enter a valid url that points to the Organization Logo. Select 'Preview' to preview the entered logo URL    | No     |
| Authorize URL     | This is an auto generated URL that could be used to obtain the Authorization Code. This is a read-only field. Select the copy button next to this URL to copy this URL to the clipboard, as shown below.    | No     |
| Access Token URL     | This is an auto generated URL that could be used to obtain the Access Token Code. This is a read-only field. Select the copy button next to this URL to copy this URL to the clipboard, as shown below. | No     |
| Application/Client Id     | This is a read-only field, displaying the unique Client Id. Select the copy button next to this, to copy this URL to the clipboard, as shown below.    | Yes     |
| Application/Client Secret     | This is a read-only field. When the Application/Client is loaded into the Edit Application screen, the Client Secret is displayed in the encrypted format. Select **Regenerate Secret** , to regenerate the Application/Client Secret. Once the Application/Client Secret is regenerated it will be displayed in 'Raw Format'. **This should be copied and safeguarded**. When the Application/Client Secret is regenerated, a copy button will display next to the generated. Once the Application is saved, this secret will be encrypted. BGL does not store the Raw Format and there is no way of retrieving the Raw Format.     | Yes    |
| Authorization Header    | This displays the Basic Authorization header which should be used to obtain the access token. This is a read only field. The value displayed in this field is Base 64 encoded. This field is visible and populated only when the secret is generated. The BGL API application will not store this field. This field is not retrivable once the application is saved. You can select the copy button to copy the Basic Authorization Header to the clipboard. Please copy and safe guard this information.    | Yes     |
| Redirect URLs     | The URL that will be used to redirect after Authorization. The first URL entered in the list will be taken as the default redirect url (which will be displayed in a different colour in the list). However, if you wish to use any other call back url in the list that you have added, then you will need to provide this in the Request for Authorization Code. At least one Redicrect URL should be added to this field. You can add up to 5 Redicrect URLs. Only valid URLs can be entered into this field.    | Yes     |
| Scope     | The API Application/Client Scope. Please see API Scopes for more details. The defaulty scope issued is 'Developer'.    | Yes     |


Select 'Save' as shown below, to update the API Application/client. The Application will be updated and you will be redirected to the Application List page.

item.name: API Rate Limits
item.description:
The BGL API endpoints are powered by the same underlying technology that powers the core SF360 and CAS360 applications. As a result, BGL's DevOps team closely monitors usage of the APIs to ensure a quality experience for all users of BGL's applications.

In order to manage the high volume of requests, the BGL API will limit the number of requests a client application can make to the BGL API based on two aspects, as per explained below.

# 1. X-Rate Daily Limit

This value indicates the number of requests a client can make on a given day. Currently this is set to unlimited in the staging envoirnment (https://api.staging.bgl360.com.au).

The response header "X-Rate-Daily-Limit-Remaining" indicates the remaining number of requests available. For every valid request made, this indicator will reduce its count by one. Zero means the available daily limit has been reached. -
If the daily limit has been exceeded, the following error will display with status - 429 Too Many Requests.

```
{
    "message": "Too Many Requests",
    "errors": [
        "You had too many requests today, the rate limit ceiling per day is 1000"
    ],
    "status": 429
}
```
Please note that any request returned with http code(status) 401 or 429 will not reduce the daily limit threshold.

# 2. X-Rate Limit

This value indicates the number of requests that can be made within a given time frame. Currently this is set to 100 per 10 minutes period in the staging envoirnment (https://api.staging.bgl360.com.au).

If the number of requests a client makes exceeds the specified X limit, the BGL API will return an error response as follows, with status - 429 Too Many Requests.

```
{
    "message": "Too Many Requests",
    "errors": [
        "You had too many requests in last 10 mins, the rate limit ceiling for every 10 mins is 100"
    ],
    "status": 429
}
```

item.name: API Application Type
item.description:
he Application Type, defines;

1. What an Application can access.
2. What is the Daily Rate Limit.
3. What is the 10mins Rate Limit.

To change your application/client type, please email api@bglcorp.com.au

The following table illustrates the Application/Client types that are currently supported and their role in the System.



| Application/Client Type| Daily Rate Limit | 10mins Rate Limit | Allowed Scopes |
| -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |
| Developer     | 1000     | 100     | developer     |
| Partner     | Unlimited     | 500     | developer, audit, investment     |
| Premium Partner     | Unlimited     | 1000     | all scopes     |

item.name: Grant Types and Expiry
item.description:
# Grant Types
Currently the BGL API only supportes the [Authorization Code grant type](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749#section-1.3.1)

# Expiry Times


| Grant/Token Type | Expiration | 
| -------- | -------- | 
| Authorization Code     | 10 mins     | 
| Access Token     | 7 Days     | 
| Refresh Token  | 30 days     |

item.name: Error Codes
item.description:
For API response, the BGL API will use conventional HTTP response codes to indicate the success or failure of an API request. The body of reponse will ususally provide more detailed information
e.g 


`{
    "error": "unauthorized",
    "error_description": "Full authentication is required to access this resource"
}
`

|HTTP Code|  Status Message |Description | 
|--|--|--|
| 200 | OK | Indicates that the request has succeeded.
| 201 | Created | Indicates that the POST request has been fulfilled and has resulted in one or more new resources being created |
| 302 | Found | Indicates that the target resourceresides temporarily under a different URI. e.g Access Code |
| 400 |Bad Request|Usually Caused by a missing or incorect Query Parameter |
|401 | Unauthorized | You are not authorized or do not have permission to access the resource |
| 403 | Forbidden | Indicates that the server understood the request but refuses to authorize it. Check Payload for more information |
| 404 | not found | Indicates that the BGL API did not find the target resource or is not willing to disclose that one exists. |
| 429 |Too Many Requests  | You’ve exceeded your 10 min or daily rate limit. |
| 500 |Internal Server Error | The request was unable to be processed due to an error with our servers.  |
|503 | Service Unavailable | BGL API is currently unable to handle the request due to a service outage or scheduled maintenance |

item.name: Request History
item.description:
This section provides you with a list of all the requests made by all the applications created by the logged in user.

Click on DEVELOPER from the main menu and then select the Request History tab, as shown below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/requestHistory.png)

The following information will be displayed on-screen:

| Column Name | Description | 
| -------- | -------- |
| Application/Client Name     | Name of the API Application or Client     | 
| Http Code     | 	The HTTP Response Code returned by the BGL API     | 
| Duration(ms)     | Number of milliseconds taken to complete the request     | 
| IP     | IP Address from which the request was made     | 
| End Point     | The requested Resource     | 
| Date Requested     | Date and Time the request was made     | 

You can click on the arrow icon for further information on that request, as shown below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/requestHistoryarrow.png)

A panel will display with more details on that request, as shown and explained below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/requesthistorydetail.png)

| Field | Description | 
| -------- | -------- | 
| Application/Client Id     | ID of the API Application or Client     | 
| Http Params     | The parameters passed for that request     | 
| Data Format     | The format of the data received from the request     | 
| Http Method     | The method used to make the request     | 
| Token Owner     | The owner of the token     | 


**Load More**

In order to view more requests, the user needs to click on the LOAD MORE button at the bottom of the list.

item.name: Request History - Search
item.description:
Type what you are looking for the in the search box, as shown below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/requestHistorymoredetails.png)

You can narrow your search by using the following search operators and symbols as shown in the Assisted Search panel:

AND
OR
NOT
*
The search operators need to input in uppercase.



|Operator | Example |
| -------- | -------- | 
| AND     | Search for requests that contains both input terms. For example, to search all requests made for the bglAPITokenTest with End Point /fund/trustees, you can type in 'bglAPITokenTest AND trustees' in the search box     | 
| OR     | Search for requests that contains one of the input terms. For example, to search all requests with either http code 400 or 500, you can type in '400 OR 500' in the search box.      | 
| NOT     | For example, to search for all requests with the Http Code '200' excluding requests from IP 218.219.218.219, you can type in '200 NOT 218.219.218.219' in the search box.      | 
| *     | This can be used as a wildcard. For example, to search all applications containing the word BGL, you can type in '*BGL*' in the search box.     |

item.name: Request History - Filters
item.description:
You can filter the list of requests using:

## Time Frame

Click on the drop-down list to select from one of the options as shown below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/requestHistoryfilters.png)

For example, selecting '''Last 7 days''' will list all the requests made during the past week.

## Quick Filters

The Quick Filters provide you with a list of pre-set filters that you can select to further narrow down the list.

Click on the **Quick Filters** icon.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/requestHistoryQuickFilters.png)

This will display a list of the filter options, as shown and explained below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/requestHistorydetailshttpcode.png)



| Filter | Description | 
| -------- | -------- | 
|Unsuccessful Request(s)    | This will display all requests that returned an error.     | 
|Successfull Request(s))    | This will display all requests that have been completed successully.     | 
|Fund Endpoints    | 	This will display only fund end points.     | 
|User Endpoints    | This will display only user end points.     | 
|Duration    | Selecting this filter will list all the requests that match the selected duration.     | 

You can select multiple filters. For example, selecting Unsuccessful Request(s) and Less than 1 second will list all requests that returned an error and took less than 1 second. You can further narrow the list by selecting Last 7 days as shown below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/requestHistorymultiplefilters.png)

item.name: API Status
item.description: The status of the BGL API and all of BGL's online services can be found at [https://status.bgl360.com.au](https://status.bgl360.com.au)

item.name: BGL User - Manage API Access
View Token(s)
item.description:
lick on **TOKEN MANAGER** from the menu. This will take the user to the **Token Manager** page, as shown below.

View Token(s) can be used to list tokens based on:

* Application Token(s) - Please see View Application Token(s)
* My Token(s) - Please see View My Token(s)


## View Application Token(s)
**Token Detail**

Select Token Manager from the main menu. This will take the user to the Token Manager page, as shown below.
![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/tokenManager.png)

Select an application from the drop-down list next to Token Manager. If the selected application has valid (not expired) access token(s), the Token Detail for that token will show on-screen. The details displayed are as follows:
![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/tokenManagerDetail.png)



## My Token(s)
**Token Detail**

From the Select Application menu, select My Tokens. This will list all the tokens that are owned by the current user, as displayed in the image below.
![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/tokenManagerDetails2.png)

item.name: View Accessible Funds by Token (Simple Fund 360)
item.description:
**Fund Listing**

In order to view funds related to a token, the tokens should be loaded in the Token Manager first. Please see View Tokens on how to load the tokens.

Once the tokens are loaded, click on a Token, that has funds attached to it, as displayed in the image below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/tokenManagerfunds.png)

Once the user clicks on the token, the Token listing will slide to the left. The funds will be loaded and displayed for the highlighted or selected token

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/tokenManager3.png)

**Back to Token View**

In order to go back to the Tokens View, click the Arrow located in the right boundary of the token box as displayed in the image below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/tokenManagerArrow.png)

item.name: Enable and Disable Funds Accessible by a Token (Simple Fund 360)
item.description:
This section goes through how you can enable and disable fund(s) accessible by a token.

From the Select Application menu, select My Tokens from the drop-down list. This will list all the tokens that are owned by the logged in user, as displayed in the image below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/myTokensDropDown.png)

Note: You cannot enable/disable funds from the View Application Token(s) page.

Click on the token for which to enable/disable funds.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/myTokensDropDowndetail.png)

This will list all the funds accessible by the token.

**Enable/Disable Fund by Fund**

To disable access to one fund, click on the green tick icon, as shown below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/disableFund.png)

To enable access to one fund, click on the green circle icon, as illustrated below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/selectFund.png)

An Unsaved label will also appear next to those funds. To confirm the changes, click on the counter. The icon will change to a SAVE CHANGES icon, as illustrated below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/tokenSaveChanges.png)

The Change Confirmation screen will display all the changes made by the user. Select **Confirm** to process all the changes made.

Alternatively, Select the Reverse icon to undo a change, as shown below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/tokenReverse.png)

You can then select Close to exit out of that box.
**
Enable/Disable All Funds
**
You can enable/disable all funds by selecting on the ... icon, as shown below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/tokenSelectAll.png)

You can then select Enable All or Disable All to enable or disable access to all funds previously authorised for that token.

A confirmation message will display depending on which option the user has selected.

Select Enable All/Disable All to process the changes.

item.name: Delete Token
item.description:
A Token can be deleted from **Application Token(s**) or from **My Token(s)** screens. In order to delete a token, the tokens should be loaded in Token Manager first. Please see View Tokens on how to load tokens.

Once the token is loaded, click on the Delete icon of the token that needs to be deleted, as displayed in the image below.

![](https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/sf360.com.au/api_images/tokenDelete.png)

The Application will display a confirmation dialog window, requesting the user to confirm the deletion of the token. 

If the user clicks "OK", the token will be deleted. If the user clicks "Cancel", the deletion will be aborted.

Further, there is a "checkbox" in the delete confirmation dialog window, as displayed in the image below.

By default, this checkbox will be ticked. This indicates that every time a deletion is performed, the confirmation will pop up. If the user unticks the "Keep this warning" checkbox and clicks "OK", the subsequent deletions will be performed without first displaying the delete confirmation dialog window.

If the deletion is successful, the user will be displayed with a success message and the token will be removed from the Token listing, displayed to the user.
The following describes how a BGL user can edit and revoke access given to Third Parties.

Allows you to retrieve a List of members for the fund, a list of accounts which they have and the account balances at the start and end of the Financial Year. 


**Account Details**

| Key | Data Type | Constraints/Description |

| accountDescription     | String     | Freeform description of pension entered by the user     |
| accountPhase     | Object     | "Accumulation" or "RetirementPhase"     |

| closingBalanceAt30June     | number     | Account Balance as at June 30 for the Financial Year requested     |
| commencementConditionOfRelease     | ConditionOfRelease     | see below     |

| conversionDate     | String     | Date pension was converted to an ABP     |

| endDate     | Date     | If account has been closed then then date is returned     |

| startDate     | Date     | The date the member account commenced in the fund     |
| taxFreeProportion     | Number     | The tax free percentage of the member's account balance will display. This amount is automatically calculated based on the taxable and tax free components of the member's balances upon pension commencement.     |

request.description:
Allows you to retrieve the Chart of Acounts based on a fund id

The chart of accounts is a list of all accounts used by a fund. It is used to further define particular classes of transactions. Each account in the chart of accounts will have its own unique account code and account name.

Detailed Help for the Chart of Accounts in Simple Fund 360  can be found [here](https://sf360.zendesk.com/hc/en-au/articles/360017815911). 

The [Chart of Accounts](https://sf360.zendesk.com/hc/en-au/articles/360017815911) has the following ranges 

| Account Type | account code range | Report Type |
| -------- | -------- |  -------- | 
| Income     | 20000 - 29999     | Operating Statement |
| Expenses     | 30000 - 47999     |Operating Statement |
| Taxation/Allocation     | 48000 - 49999     | Operating Statement |
| Member Accounts     | 50000 - 59999     | Balance Sheet |
| Other Assets     | 60000 - 69999     |Balance Sheet |
| Investments     | 70000 - 79999     | Balance Sheet |
| Liabilities     | 80000 - 89999     | Balance Sheet |
| Suspense     | 90000 - 99999     | Balance Sheet |

Refer to [Master Chart of Accounts](https://sf360.zendesk.com/hc/en-au/articles/360017532172-Global-Chart-of-Accounts) for a detailed listing of the Chart of Accounts

request.description:
Allows you to retrieve a the type of Trustee, Corporate Trustee Details (if applicable) and a List of Individual Trustees/Directors based on a Fund ID. 
Each addressId and peopleId will be unique for the firm and can be used to avoid duplicates. 

**corporateDetails Object**

Corporate details will only exist if Trustee Type is equal to Corporate. 

| Key | Data Type | Contraints/Description|
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| acn     | String     | ACN of company     |
| addressId     | String     | UniqueID of address for a firm. If address is used for multiple people or companies the id will be the same.   |
| companyId     | String     | UniqueID of the company for a firm.     |
| corporateName     | String     | Name of Corporate Trustee     |
| country     | String     | Address - Country     |
| email     | String     | email address if known     |
| phone     | String     | phone number if known     |
| postcode     | String     | Address - Postcode     |
| state     | object     | List in ( VIC, NSW, QLD, WA, NSW, ACT, TAS, FOR)     |
| streetLine1     | String     | Address - Street Line 1    |
| streetLine2     | String     | Address - Street Line 2   |
| suburb     | String     | Address - Suburb  |
     

**trusteeOrDirector Array**

| Key | Data Type | Contraints/Description|
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| addressId     | String     | UniqueID of address for a firm. If address is used for multiple people or companies the id will be the same.   |
| country     | String     | Address - Country     |
| dob     | Date     | ISO 8601 date https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601     |
| email     | String     | email address if known    |
| firstName     | String     |Person's first name    |
| lastName     | String     |Person's last name    |
| otherName     | String     |Person's other/middle names    |
| peopleId     | String     | UniqueID of person for a firm. If person is used for multiple companies or funds the id will be the same. |
| phone     | String     | phone number if known     |
| postcode     | String     | Address - Postcode     |
| state     | object     | List in ( VIC, NSW, QLD, WA, NSW, ACT, TAS, FOR)     |
| streetLine1     | String     | Address - Street Line 1    |
| streetLine2     | String     | Address - Street Line 2   |
| suburb     | String     | Address - Suburb  |
| title     | String     | Title if known  |

request.description:
Get Ledger Transactions for a fundId

### Query Parameters

| Form Parameter | type | Mandatory | Description |
| -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |
| start     | date     | Yes     |   End date of Report. Expected format : yyyy-mm-dd |
| end | date | Yes | End date of Report.  Expected format : yyyy-mm-dd |
|modifiedSince | date | No | Expected format : yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ss. Example = 2019-04-05T14:30.15. Only transactions where the dateLastUpdated is after this date and time will be returned. |
|modifiedBefore |date | No | Expected format : yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ss. Example = 2019-04-05T14:30.15. Only transactions where the dateLastUpdated is before this date and time will be returned. |

### Response Body
  
 |Key  |Datatype  | Constraints/Comments |
 |--|--|--|
 |accountClass | String | From list (N = "Normal",C = "Control") | 
 |accounts | Array | see Below
 |code | String  | The Account Code of the Account (Normal or Control) from the Chart of Accounts | 
 |name | String  | The name of the Account (Normal or Control) from the Chart of Accounts   | 
   

**accounts array**

 | Key  | Datatype  | Constraints/Comments | 
 |  --  | --  | --  | 
 | accountId | string |Chart of Accounts Id account. | 
 | accountType | string | Chart of Accounts sub-type of account. | 
 | amountTotal  | number  | The total of all of transactions returned based on the query parameters for the account.  | 
 | entryTransactions  | Array  | Array of Transactions for the account. See Below.  | 
 | securityCode  | String  | For Investments, the linked Security Code.| 
 | subCode  | String  | The Account Code of the Sub-Account from the Chart of Accounts. If AccountClass is equal to Normal then will be empty. |
 | subName  | String  | The name of the Sub-Account from the Chart of Accounts. If AccountClass is equal to Normal then will be empty. |
 | unitsTotal  | number  | The total of all of units returned based on the parameters for the account.  | 
 

**entryTransactions array**

 | Key  | Datatype  | Constraints/Comments  | 
 |  --  | --  |  --  | 
 |  amount  | number  | amount of the Transaction  |
 |createSource| String | How transaction was created in SF360 | 
 |createdBy  | String  | Who transaction was created by  | 
 | createdTime  | Date  | Date and Time transaction was created  |
 | description | String  | Transaction Description/narration | 
 | entryId  | String  | Unique Transaction ID  | 
 | lastModifiedTime  | Date  | Date and Time transaction was last modified.|
 | sourceType  | String  | Method of how transactions was created  | 
 | transactionDate  |  date  | The date of the transaction  | 
 | transactionId  | String  | Linked Transaction ID   | 
 | transactionType  | String  | List From (BankStatement, GeneralJournal, SystemJournal)  | 
 | units  | number  | Units for the Transaction or Balance  |

request.description:
Will retrieve form lodgement history with the ATO for a fund. 

### Response Body

| Key| Mandatory|Description |
| -------- | -------- | -------- | 
 | form | String | Name of the form. returns either "SMSF_ANNUAL_RETURN" or"ACTIVITY_STATEMENT" |
|lodgementDateTime |Date |Date and time the form was lodged (UTC) |
|lodgementStatus | String | Status of the form | 
|lodgingPartyFirm | String | Name of lodging party who is responsible for the form |
|lodgingPartyIndividual | String | Individuals name of lodging party who is responsible for the form |
| validatedDateTime | Date | Date and time the form was validated (UTC)|
| year | Date | Year of the form. format = YYYY | 

**Lodgement Statuses**

| Status | Description |
| -------- | -------- |
| LODGED_ELE | Lodged electronically/manually |
| LODGED_REJ | Lodgment Rejected | 
| VALIDATED | Form Validated | 
| null | When the form is only prepared it will send status as null |

request.description:
The Contribution Breakdown Report provides a detailed summary view of all member contribution accounts for the period. The report will detail:

* Member, date of birth and age;
* Each member and their contributions for the year (concessional, non-concessional, other, reserves);
* Contribution caps for concessional, non-concessional and the three year non-concessional bring forward amounts if triggered;
* Complete transaction list of all contributions for all members
* Contribution totals for all members;
* A SuperStream column allowing you to compare member contribution ledger data with actual SuperStream data. 
* Employer shown in SuperStream data column
The report can also be used to reconcile the total contribution amount for the fund appearing in account 24200 in the operating statement. 

### Response

| Key | datatype | Constraints/description |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| members     | Array     | See Members array below     |
| totalConcessionalForAllMembers     | number     |    |
| members    | object     |  see below  |
| totalNon-concessionalForAllMembers  | number     |    |
| totalOtherForAllMembers   |   number     |    |
| totalReservesForAllMembers  | number     |    |
| totalContributionsForAllMembers   | number     |    |

**Members object**

| Key | datatype | Constraints/description |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| age     | Array     |  Member's Age as at start of Financial Year  |
| dob     | Date     |  Format = yyyy-MM-dd  |
| firstName     | String     |  Person’s first name  |
| lastName     | String     |  Person’s first name  |
| downsizerAmount     | number     | The Downsizer Contributions recorded for the member for the Financial Year   |
| downsizerCap     | number     | The Downsizer Contributions Cap for the member for the Financial Year   |
| nonConcessionalCap     | number     |  The Non-Concessional Contributions Cap for the member for the Financial Year  |
| openingDownsizer     | number     | The total Downsizer Contributions made in prior Financial Years   |
| otherName     | string     | Person’s other/middle names. |
| peopleId     | string     | UniqueID of person for a firm. |
| contactId     | String     |  UniqueID of person is used for a company  |
| totalConcessional     |  number    | The total Concessional Contributions recorded for the member for the Financial Year   |
| totalNonConcessional     |   number   | The total Non-Concessional Contributions recorded for the member for the Financial Year    |
| totalOther     |   number   |  The Other contributions recorded for the member for the Financial Year  |
| totalReserves     |   number  |  The contributions which have been allocated to a reserve recorded for the member for the Financial Year  |
| totalSuperstreamConcessional   |  number    | The total Concessional Contributions received via SuperStream the member for the Financial Year   |
| totalSuperstreamNonConcessional     |  number     | The total Non-Concessional Contributions received via SuperStream the member for the Financial Year   |
| tsbOfPriorFY     |  number    |  The Total Super Balance of the person as at 30 June of the previous Financial Year. Note this is only as accurate as the data within Simple Fund 360 and may not contain data about non-SMSFs  |
| contributionCapSummary     |  Array    | see below  |
| nccBringForwardCap     |  Object    | see below   |
| members     |  Array    |  See below  |
| superStream     |  Array  | same as ledgerData array |   

**contributionCapSummary Array**

| Key | datatype | Constraints/description |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| contributionType     | string     | List from (Concessional, Non-Concessional, Downsizer)  |
| capEndDate     | date     | format = yyyy-MM-dd |
| contributions     | number     | The total Contributions recorded for the member for the Financial Year |
| cap     | number     | The Contributions Cap for the member for the Financial Year |
| currentPositionAmount     | number    | 0 will indicate the member is at their limit, a positive number will be how much they are over their cap and a negative number will be how much is remaining in the cap|  |
| currentPositionLabel     | string     | List from (UnderCap, OverCap, AtLimit, TSBOverTBC) |

**nccBringForwardCap Object**

| Key | datatype | Constraints/description |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| bringForwardCap     | number     |  Current Bring forward Cap for  the member for the Financial Year  |
| bringForwardTriggeredYear     | date     | format = yyyy. The Financial Year for the total Non-Concessional Cap has triggered the Bring Forward Rule    |
| Year1     | date     |The  Financial Year 3 years ago    |
| year1Amount    | number | The total Non-Concessional Contributions recorded for the member for the Financial Year 3 years ago     |    |
| Year2     | date     | The  Financial Year 2 years ago   |
| year2Amount     | number     | The total Non-Concessional Contributions recorded for the member for the Financial Year 2 years ago   |
| Year3     | Date     |  The  Previous Financial Year  |
| year3Amount     | number     | The total Non-Concessional Contributions recorded for the member for the previous Financial Year   |
| Year4     | Date     | The Current Financial Year    |
| year4Amount     | number     |  The total Non-Concessional Contributions recorded for the member for the Financial Year  |
| totalAmount     | number     | The total Non-Concessional Contributions recorded for the member for Bring Forward Period   |
| currentPositionLabel     | string     | From List (UnderCap,  OverCap ,  AtLimit, TSBOverTBC)   |

**ledgerData array**

| Key | datatype | Constraints/description |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| date |date |	The date of the transaction or SuperStream data |
|description |	string	| The Transaction Description|
|contributionType | string| The SuperStream Contribution Type |
|concessional | number |	The amount of the contribution classified as Concessional |
|non-concessional| number	|The amount of the contribution classified as Non-Concessional |
|other |	number	|The amount of the contribution classified as an Other Contribution |
|reserves	|number	|The amount of the contribution allocated to Reserves|

request.description:
The Contribution Summary displays all contribution amounts, contributions cap limits, details of NCC Bring Forward cap if triggered) of all active members for a particular financial year. 

### Response
|Key|Data Type|Description|
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
|fundId|String|Id of the fund|
|financialYear|Number|Financial year of the contributions|
|contributions|List of Contribution|List of contributions|

#### Contribution

|Key|Data Type|Description|
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
|peopleId|String|Id of the person|
|firstName|String|First name|
|lastName|String|Last name|
|birthday|Date|Date of birth|
|memberAccountId|Number|Member account ID|
|memberAccountCode|String|Member account code|
|memberAccountStartDate|Date|Start date of the member account|
|memberAccountEndDate|String|End date of the member account. This key will only be returned if an end date is present. |
|contributionAccountId|Number|Chart Id of the member's contribution account |
|openingDownsizer|Number|Total Downsizer Contributions made until the end of the previous financial year|
|downsizerAmount|Number|Downsizer Contributions recorded for the financial year|
|downsizerCap|Number|Downsizer Contributions Cap for the financial year|
|concessionalContributions|Array|List of Concessional Contributions listed below|
|nonConcessionalContributions|Array|List of Non-Concessional Contribution listed below|
|totalSuperBalances|Array|List of Total Super Balances listed below|

#### Concessional Contributions Array

|Key|Data Type|Description|
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
|financialYear|Number|Financial year of this concessional contributions|
|amount|Number|Concessional Contributions recorded for the financial year|
|cap|Number|General Concessional Contributions cap for the financial year|
|carryForwardOrigins|Array|Remaining balance of Unused Concessional Contributions cap for each previous financial year|
|unusedCap|Number|Unused Amount of Concessional Contributions cap |
|cumulativeCarryForward|Number|Total unused cap carried forward (i.e. sum of all the amounts in carryForwardOrigins)|
|maxCap|Number|Maximum Concessional Contributions the member is eligible to contribute|
|position|Number|Balance to reach/exceeded the maximum Concessional Contributions cap available (i.e. amount - maxCap)|
|labels|String[]|"Status of the member's Concessional Contributions made (e.g. UnderCap, OverCap, ApproachingCap, AtLimit, CFTriggered)"|

#### Non-Concessional Contribution Array

|Key|Data Type|Description|
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
|financialYear|Number|Financial year of this Non-Concessional Contribution|
|amount|Number|Non-Concessional Contribution recorded for the financial year|
|cap|Number|Non-Concessional Contribution cap for the financial year|
|position|Number|Balance to reach/exceeded the Non-Concessional Contribution cap (i.e. amount - cap)|
|labels|String[]|"Status of the member's Non-Concessional Contribution made (e.g. UnderCap, OverCap, ApproachingCap, AtLimit, BFTriggered)"|
|bringForwardTriggerYear|Number|Optional. Financial year in which the Bring Forward Rule for member's Non-Concessional Contribution is triggered|
|bringForwardOrder|Number|Optional. Financial year order in the bring forward period|
|bringForwardCap1|Number|Optional. Bring Forward cap|
|bringForwardDate1|Date|Optional. Expiry date of the above Bring Forward cap 1|
|bringForwardCap2|Number|Optional. Only available when the bring forward trigger year is FY2016 and FY2017|
|bringForwardDate2|Date|Optional. Expiry date of the above Bring Forward cap 2|

#### Total Super Balance Array
|Key|Data Type|Description|
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
|financialYear|Number|Financial year of this Total Super Balance|
|amount|Number|Total Super Balance as at end of the previous financial year. (as at 30/06/2018 if financial year field is 2019)|

query.description: [REQUIRED] Financial Year of Report. Expected format : YYYY

request.description:
Allows you to retrieve the Detailed Statement of Financial Position (or Balance Sheet) for a specific fund. 

The Detailed Statement of Financial Position provides comprehensive information of each:

Investment; and
Asset; and
Liability
account of the fund grouped according to the general ledger account to which they belong.

This gives a further breakdown of the accounts of the fund and identifies which control account they fall under. 

[Example of Detailed Statement of Financial Position (PDF)](https://360help.com.au/display/SF360GS/Detailed+Statement+of+Financial+Position?preview=%2F25006034%2F25006510%2FDetailed+Balance+Sheet.pdf)

* If you require a Summarised Balance Sheet all entries under each subEntries element can be ignored.
* If you require a Detailed Balance Sheeet all entries under each subEntries element are required.

| Key | Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| financialYear     | Date     | Current Financial Year of Report     |
| financialYearPrev     | Date     | Financial Year of Comparatives     |
| fundName     | string     |  the name of the Fund    |
| investmentList     | array     | see Account array below     |
| investmentTotal     | number     | The total balance of all Investments in the financialYear     |
| investmentTotalPrev     | string     | The total balance of all Investments in the financialYearPrev      |
| otherAssets     | array     | Assets of the fund which are not Investments for the current Financial year. see Account array below     |
| otherAssetsPrev     | array     | Assets of the fund which are not Investments for the previouis Financial year. see Account array below     |
| totalOtherAssets     | number     | Total of assets of the fund which are not Investments for the current Financial year. see Account array below     |
| totalOtherAssetsPrev     | number     | Total of sssets of the fund which are not Investments for the previouis Financial year. see Account array below     |
| totalAssets     | number     | equal to investmentTotal + totalOtherAssets for the current Financial Year   |
| totalAssetsPrev     | number     | equal to investmentTotal + totalOtherAssets for the previous Financial Year  |
| liabilities     | array     | see Account array below     |
| totalLiabilities     | number     | Total of Liabilities for current Financial Year     |
| totalLiabilitiesPrev     | number     | Total of Liabilities for previous Financial Year     |
| netAssetsAvailable     | number     | Net assets available to pay benefits for current Financial year. Equal to investmentTotal + totalAssets less totalLiabilities     |
| netAssetsPrev    | number     | Net assets available to pay benefits for previous Financial year. Equal to investmentTotal + totalAssets less totalLiabilities     |
| liabilitiesForAccruedBenefits     | array     | Member's Balances. see Account array below     |
| totalLiabilitiesForAccruedBenefits     | number     | Total Liability for accrued benefits allocated to members' accounts for current Financial year.     |
| totalLiabilitiesForAccruedBenefitsPrev    | number     | Total Liability for accrued benefits allocated to members' accounts for previous Financial year.      |
| netAssetLessAccruedLiability     | number     | Net Assets less liabilities less netAssetLessAccuredLiability for current Financial year. If this feild is not equal to zero then it indicates Balance Sheet is out of Balance.   |
| netAssetLessAccruedLiabilityPrev     | number     | Net Assets less liabilities less netAssetLessAccuredLiability for previous Financial Year. If this feild is not equal to zero then it indicates Balance Sheet is out of Balance.   |
| sofpNotBalancedEntries     | array     | Balances of Accounts such as suspense accounts which would cause the Balance Sheet to not Balance. see Account array below     |


**Account array**

| Key | Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| accountCode     | String     | The Account Code from the Chart of Accounts. Display Control Account code for Control Accounts. Display Sub-account code for sub-accounts.    |
| amount     | Date     | Balance of the Chart Category (Control Account) in the financialYear    |
| amountPrev     | Date     | Balance of the Chart Category (Control Account) in the financialYearPrev     |
| name     | string     | the name of the account from the [Chart of Accounts](https://bglapi.restlet.io/#operation_chart_of_accounts)     |
| subEntries     | array     | Follows the same format as the Account array. This is only needed if you require a Detailed Balance sheet     |

request.description:
The Detailed Operating Statement is a statement of Investment Income, Contribution Income, Investment Gains, Expenses and Member Payments showing the results of an SMSF's  operations for a period. 

* If you require a Summarised Operating Statement all entries under each  **subEntries**  or **items**  element can be ignored.
* If you require a Detailed Operating Statement all entries under each **subEntries**  or **items** element are required.

| Key | Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| fundName     | string     |  the name of the fund   |
| fundDate     | string     |  description of the Financial Period     |
| financialYear     | Date     | Current Financial Year of Report     |
| financialYearPrev     | Date     | Financial Year of Comparatives     |
| income     | Accounts array     | see Accounts array below     |
| expenses     | Accounts array     | see Accounts array below     |
| taxExpense     | Accounts array     | see Accounts array below     |
| totalMarketMovement     | number     | The total Change in Market Movement in the financialYear     |
| totalMarketPrev     | number     | The total Change in Market Movement in the financialYearPrev      |
| incomeTotal     | number     | The total Income for the the financialYear     |
| IncomeTotalPrev     | number     | The total income for the financialYearPrev      |
| expenseTotal     | number     | The total Expenses for the the financialYear     |
| expenseTotalPrev     | number     | The total Expenses for the financialYearPrev      |
| accruedBenefitsBeforeIncTax     | number     | The total Benefits accrued as a result of operations before income tax for the the financialYear     |
| accruedBenefitsBeforeIncTaxPrev     | number     | The total Benefits accrued as a result of operations before income tax for the financialYearPrev      |
| incomeTaxTotal     | number     | The total income tax for the the financialYear     |
| incomeTaxTotalPrev     | number     | The income tax for the financialYearPrev      |
| benefitsAccuredResultOp     | number     | The total Benefits accrued as a result of operations for the the financialYear       |
| benefitsAccuredResultOpPrev     | number     |The total Benefits accrued as a result of operations for the financialYearPrev       |

**Accounts array**

| Key | Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| mainName     | string     | Investment Category from the [Chart of Accounts](https://bglapi.restlet.io/#operation_chart_of_accounts)     |
| title     | string     | The name of the control or normal account from the [Chart of Accounts](https://bglapi.restlet.io/#operation_chart_of_accounts)    |
| mainTitle     | string     | name of Operating Statement Section    |
| totalAmount     | number     | Total of the Chart Category (Control Account) in the financialYear    |
| totalAmountPrev     | number     | Total of the Chart Category (Control Account) in the financialYearPrev     |
| items     | array     | Refer to Items Array below | 

**items array**

| Key | Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| amount     | number     | Total of the account in the financialYear    |
| amountPrev     | number     | Total of the account in the financialYearPrev     |
| name     | string     | the name of the account from the [Chart of Accounts](https://bglapi.restlet.io/#operation_chart_of_accounts)     |
| subEntries     | string     | Follows the same format as the the above three fields.  |

request.description:
Allows you to retrieve an General Ledger for one a fund

### Response

**generalLedger array**

| Key | Data Type  | Description/Contraints |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| fundId     | string     | The Unique ID of the Fund. This is unique across all funds on Simple Fund 360   |
| start     | Date     | The Start Date of Report     |
| end     | Date     | The end date of the report     |
|data |Array| See Below  |

**data array**

| Key | Data Type  | Description/Contraints |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| fundName     | string     | The name of the Fund |
| fromDate     | Date     | The start date of the report |
| toDate     | Date     | the end date of the report |
| year     | Date     | The year of the report |
| id     | Object     | |
| accountClass     | object     | C = Control, S = Sub-account, N= Normal |
| fundId     | string     | The unique ID of the fund |
| taccountParentName     | string     | The name of the control account from the Chart of Accounts |
| taccountParentCode     | string     | The account Code of the control account from the Chart of Accounts |

| description     | string     | Transaction Description/narration |
| units     | number     | Units for the Transaction or Balance |

| balance     | number     | running balance for the transaction |
| bankFeedsProvider     | string     | Data feed source for the transaction |

query.description: [REQUIRED] The Financial Year of the  report. Expected format : yyyy

request.description:
Allows you to retrieve Investment Movement report data for fund based on a Financial Year

### Response


**Fund Data**

| Field | Data Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
|additionsCostTotals| number | The sum of all additions to the Investment's Cost bases for the fund |
|closingBalanceCostTotals|  number | The sum of all closing balances Investment's Cost bases for the fund |
|closingBalanceMarketValueTotals | number |The sum of all Investment's Market Values for the fund|
|disposalsAccountProfitOrLossTotals| number| The sum of all accounting gains/losses for all disposals for the fund |
|disposalsCostTotals| number |The sum of all disposals for  the fund  |
|investments|  Array |  see below|
|openingBalanceCostTotals| number|The sum of all Opening Balances for Investments for the fund |

**Investment Array**

| Field | Data Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
|additionsCostTotals| number | The sum of all additions to the Investment |
|closingBalanceCostTotals|  number | The sum of all closing balances Investment |
|closingBalanceMarketValueTotals | number |The sum of all Investment's Market Value for the Investment|
|disposalsAccountProfitOrLossTotals| number| The sum of all accounting gains/losses for all disposals for the Investment |
|disposalsCostTotals| number |The sum of all disposals for  the Investment  |
|investmentdetailsList|  Array |  see below|
|openingBalanceCostTotals| number |The sum of all Opening Balances for the Investments |
|parentInvestmentAccCode| string |The sum of all Opening Balances for the Investment |
|parentInvestmentName| string |The sum of all Opening Balances for  the Investment |

**investmentdetailsList Array**

| Field | Data Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
|transactionType | String | Transaction line from list of (additions, closingBalance, disposals, investmentCode) |
| accountingProfitOrLoss | number| Where transactionType = disposals this will be accounting gain or loss | 
| cost | number | The balance or movement to the cost base of the Investment | 
| marketValue | number | The Clsoing Market value of the Investment | 
| units | number | The balance or movement in units for the Investment |

request.description:
Allows you to retrieve a Pension Sumary for  fund based on a Financial Year.

### Response


**Fund Data**

| Field | Data Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| financialYear     | date     | YYYY - The financial year of the report     |
| fundName     | string     | The name of the fund     |
| fundId     | Text     | The Fund Identificaion Number. This is unique across all of Simple Fund 360.    |
| fundAmountToReachMinimum     | number     | The total amount required for the fund to reach the minimum for all pensions.   |
| fundGrossPensionPayments     | number     | The total pension payments recorded for all pension members of the fund     |
| fundMinimum     | number     | The combined minimum amount for all pension members of the fund      |
| fundPensionPayments     | number     | The total pension payments recorded for all pension members of the fund less PAYG.    |
| fundPayg     | number     | The total PAYG withheld which has been recorded for all pension members    |
| pensions     | array     | see below     |

**Pensions Array**

 | Field | Data Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| peopleId     | string     | Unique Identifier of person in Simple Fund 360     |
| contactId     | string     | Unique Identifier of person in Simple Fund 360     |
| accounts     | array     | see below     |

**Accounts Array**

 | Field | Data Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| accountDescription     | string     | Description entered by the user for the Pension Account     |
| accountPhase     | string     | will return either "Retirement Phase" or "Accumulation"     |
| amountToReachMinimum     | number     | number of dollars required for this pension to reach the minimum     |
| endDate     | date     | yyyy-MM-dd : The end date of the pension if the account ceased during the Financial Year of the report.      |
| grossPensionPayments     | number     | The total pension payments recorded for this pension account for the Financial Year   |
| memberCode     | string     | The member code assigned to this Pension Account. This will also be equal to the sub-account code on other APIs     |
| minimum     | number     | The Minimum Pension amount required for this Pension Account for the Financial Year.      |
| maximum     | number     | The Maximum Pension amount (if applicable) required for this Pension Account for the Financial Year.      |
| netPensionPayments     | number     | The total pension payments recorded for this pension account for the Financial Year  less PAYG payments     |
| note   | string     | Addtional details were pensionhas reverted   |
| openingBalance     | number     | The Balanace of the account as at July 1st of the Financial Year or the Penson startDate if the income stream commenced during the Financial Year.      |
| payg     | number     | The total PAYG amount withheld which has been recorded this Pension Account for the Financial Year.      |
| pensionType     | string     | Type of Pension     |
| reversionAccountCode     | string     | The Account Code, the Pension reverted from.      |
| reversionDate     | date     | Date original Pension reverted to Beneficiary    |
| reversionaryPensionDateOfDeath     | Date     | Date of death for orignal pension member    |
| startDate     | date     | The Start Date of this Pension     |
| taxFreeProportion     | number     | The Tax Free proportion recorded for this Pension Account     |

request.description:
Allows you to retrieve the Trial Balance for a specified fund id. 

### Response


**trialbalance array**

| Key | Data Type  | Description/Contraints |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| fundId     | string     | The Unique ID of the Fund. This is unique across all funds on Simple Fund 360   |
| start     | Date     | The Start Date of Report     |
| end     | Date     | The end date of the report     |

**Data Array.** 

Refer to [Chart of Accounts](https://bglapi.restlet.io/#operation_chart_of_accounts) for details on the Chart of Accounts in SF360.  |

| Key | Data Type  | Description/Contraints |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| accountClass     | Object     | C = Control, S = Sub-account, N= Normal   
| accountCode     | String     | The Account Code from the Chart of Accounts.  |
| accountType     | String     | The Account Type from the Chart of Accounts.      |
| minCode     | Number     | The minimum account code used by the accountType     |
| maxCode     | Number     | The minimum account code used by the accountType      |
| name     | string     | The name of the account from the Chart of Accounts     |
| units     | Number (nullable     | The Number of Units on hand as at the End Date. Only used if accountType is Investment   |
| debits     | Number (nullable)     | The Debit Balance of the account as at the End Date.     |
| credits     | Number (nullable)     | The Credit Balance of the account as at the End Date    |
| unitsPrev     | Number (nullable)     | The Number of Units on hand as at the Start Date. Only used if accountType is Investment  |
| debitsPrev     | Number (nullable)     | The Debit Balance of the account as at the Start Date.     |
| creditsPrev     | Number (nullable)     | The Credit Balance of the account as at the Start Date       |
| balancePrev     | Number (nullable)     | The Balance of the account as at the Start Date. A Positive number equals a debit balance. A credit balance equals a Credit balance     |

### Request

|Key | Type | Mandatory | Description/Constraints |
| -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |
| name     | String     | Yes     |  Name of the fund  |
| dateFormed  | Date    | Yes     | Date format is yyyy-MM-dd   |


### Response Body

|Key | Type | Mandatory | Description/Constraints |
| -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |
| name     | String     | Yes     |  The Name of the SMSF  |
| fundCode     | String     | No     | If not supplied the field will be auto-created by Simple Fund 360   |
| abn     | number     | No     | If supplied, the number must be valid ABN   |
| tfn     | number     | No     | If supplied must be valid TFN   |
| dateFormed     | date     | Yes     | Must in format yyyy-MM-dd   |
| financialYearFrom     | date     | Yes     | If not supplied, system will default to dateFormed. Cannot be before dateFormed. Must in format yyyy-MM-dd   |
| financialYearEnd     | date     | Yes     |  If not supplied, system will default to next 30 June date after dateFormed. Cannot be before dateFormed. Must in format yyyy-MM-dd   |

request.description:
Using a FundId an API Consumer can add or update Fund Details. 

### Request

|Key | Type | Mandatory | Description/Constraints |
| -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |
| badgeId     | Number     | No     |  Must be a valid badge id for the firm  |
| name     | String     | No     |  The Name of the SMSF  |
| fundCode     | String     | No     | If not supplied the field will be auto-created by Simple Fund 360   |
| abn     | number     | No     | If supplied, the number must be valid ABN   |
| tfn     | number     | No     |  If supplied must be valid TFN |
| esa     | String     | No     |  Electronic Service Address  |
| dateFormed     | date     | No     | Must in format yyyy-MM-dd   |
| windUpDate     | date     | No     | Must in format yyyy-MM-dd   |
| financialYearFrom     | date     | No     | If not supplied, system will default to dateFormed. Cannot be before dateFormed. Must in format yyyy-MM-dd   |
| financialYearEnd     | date     | No     |  If not supplied, system will default to next 30 June date after dateFormed. Cannot be before dateFormed. Must in format yyyy-MM-dd   |
| systemStartDate     | date     | No     |  Must be present if enteringOpeningBalance = Yes. Cannot be before dateFormed. Must in format yyyy-MM-dd   |
| enteringOpeningBalance     | Boolean     | No     |  True or False |
| postalAddress     | Array     | No     | see Address Array below  |
| physicalAddress     | Array     | No     | see Address Array below  |
| trustDeedSource    | String     | No     |   |
| trustDeedLastModifiedDate    | date     | No     |  Must in format yyyy-MM-dd  |
| trustDeedRuleClauseDeathBenefit    | String     | No     |    |

**Address Array**

| Key | Type | Mandatory | Constraints/Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |
| streetLine1     | String     | Yes     | Mandatory if any other address fields are not empty	  |
| streetLine2     | String     | No     | 	  |
| city     | String     | Yes     | Mandatory if any other address fields are not empty	  |
| state     | String     | Yes     | Mandatory if any other address fields are not empty. Must be one of (ACT’/‘NSW’/‘VIC’/‘QLD’/‘SA’/‘WA’/‘TAS’/‘NT)	  |
|  postCode    | String     | Yes     | Mandatory if any other address fields are not empty	  |
| country     | String     | Yes     | Mandatory if any other address fields are not empty. Must be a country code as defined in https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1_alpha-2	  |

item.description:
To create a new fund in Simple Fund 360, the following is the path is what an API consumer will need to follow:

-   Use [INSERT Fund](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#5a1896dc-7bd5-4ddc-8de5-c230672447e7) to create the Fund. This will return a FundId which can be used to insert or update any other necessary details
-   Use [UPDATE Fund Details](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#78544ec2-7bd4-42b5-aa8d-a11d4d50fae9) (using the FundId created at Step 1) to check or update Fund Details.
-   Use [CREATE Fund Contacts](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#0ecda1a1-f883-4cea-ac1d-a63c63c46bf6) (using the FundId created at Step 1) to create the Corporate Trustee, Corporate Trustee Directors or Individual Trustees.
-   Use [CREATE Member](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#a79062c6-6ea1-4778-96f0-e541e2557e19)  using FundId created at Step 1) to add members to the fund using the contacts added at Step 3.

For an  API  Consumer to check what they have created:

-   [GET Fund Details](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#ecad8545-e4bb-4722-9c64-ab6a619b0165)
-   [GET Fund Trustees](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#df029f2a-580f-4f53-8897-1ec108b2abab)
-   [GET Fund Members](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#d409fb0d-00ed-4317-b55e-27b392899de4)
-   [GET Fund Contacts](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#896c5876-11d3-4c36-b2cc-206bacb549ea)

request.description:
Allows you to retrieve the Workpapers for a specific fund. 

The Workpapers screen in Simple Fund 360 allows a user to store documents and record all evidence obtained during the preparation of the financial statements whilst ensuring the SMSF complies with all relevant laws during the Financial Year. 

For full details on what users can do on this screen in Simple Fund 360 please consult our [Help Guide](https://sf360.zendesk.com/hc/en-au/articles/360033852392-Workpapers)


### Response Body 

| Key | Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| code     | Date     | Code of Workpaper. This will usually be the Control Account from the Chart of Accounts   |
| description     | String     | Name of the account from the Chart of Accounts   |
| amount     | Number     | Balance of the account as at the end of the Financial Year   |
| amountPrev     | Number     |Balance of the account as at the end of the Previous Financial Year    |
| units     | Number     | Balance of the number of units for the account as at the end of the Financial Year    |
| unitsPrev     | Number     | Balance of the number of units for the account as at the end of the Previous Financial Year  |
| change     | Number     | Difference between amount and amountPrev as a percentage  |
| status     | String     | Status of the Workpapers  |
| preparer     | String     | Name of  person who prepared Workpaper  |
| reviewer     | String     | Name of person who prepared Workpaper   |
| documents     | Array     | Documents assigned to Workpapers. Documents which have been assigned to a Sub-Account will be listed under the subEntries or memberSubEntries Array   |
| subEntries     | Array     |Details for Sub-Accounts where they exist    |
| memberSubEntries     | Array     | For member accounts (Chart Codes 50000 - 58000) |

**documents array**

| Field | Data Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
|name | string | name of the file/document from Simple Fund 360 |
| key | string | Unique Identifier of the document. Documents can be downloaded using the [Download Documents Endpoint](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#cf51ff1e-8b5d-48cc-be66-cbf275996e1f)|
| creationDate | Date | Date and Time date the file was added to Simple Fund 360 |
| updatedDate | Date | Date and Time date the file was last modified |

**subEntries array**

| Key | Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| code     | Date     | Code of Workpaper. This will usually be the sub-account from the Chart of Accounts   |
| description     | String     | Name of the sub-account from the Chart of Accounts   |
| amount     | Number     | Balance of the sub-account as at the end of the Financial Year   |
| amountPrev     | Number     |Balance of the sub-account as at the end of the Previous Financial Year    |
| units     | Number     | Balance of the number of units for the sub-account as at the end of the Financial Year    |
| unitsPrev     | Number     | Balance of the number of units for the sub-account as at the end of the Previous Financial Year  |
| change     | Number     | Difference between amount and amountPrev as a percentage  |
| documents     | Array     | Documents which have been assigned to a Sub-Account  |

**memberSubEntries array**

| Key | Type | Comments |
| -------- | -------- | -------- |
| code     | Date     | Code of Workpaper. This will  be the member code  |
| description     | String     | Name of the Member Account, Member Mode and Description from the Chart of Accounts   |
| amountOpeningBalance     | Number     | Balance of account 50010 for the Financial Year   |
| amountContributionIncome     | Number     | Balance  of accounts 52420,52850,53900 & 56100 for the Financial Year   |
| amountEarnings     | Number     | Balance of account 53100  for the Financial Year     |
| amountMemberPayments     | Number     | Balance accounts 53920, 53940, 53960, 53980, 54050, 54160, 54500, 57100 & 58000 for the Financial Year    |
| amountTaxFees     | Number     | Balance of accounts 51900, 53330, 53500, 53800, 54000, 55100 & 55700  for the Financial Year    |
| amountClosingBalance     | Number     | Sum of all accounts for the Financial Year    |
| change     | Number     | Difference between Opening Balance and Closing Balance as a percentage  |
| documents     | Array     | Documents which have been assigned to a Member Sub-Account  |

request.description:
This endpoint allows a user of a particular fund to upload a new document into the fund, along with the list of tags (optional) to be associated to the newly uploaded document.
At the time of development, the following file tyle extensions are not supported for documents upload to SF360 system: exe, app, bat, dmg, and cmd.

### Request 

The multi-part request body has two form parameters


| Form Parameter | type | Mandatory | Example |
| -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |
| document     | File     | Yes     | document.pdf
| tags     | Text     | No     | ["audit"]

    fund.     
 2. Download Document - Use to download a document using the
    document ID obtained from the Document List.

This section lists the currently available resources for Simple Fund 360  that can be used to obtain data through the BGL API.
