request.description:
Gets a list of all non-deleted companies which the user has access to 

### Query Parameters

| Form Parameter | type | Mandatory | Description |
| -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |
| offset | number | Required | Example = 0 |
| limit | number | Required | Example = 500 |
|details | String | Optional | Example = true | 



### Response Body

Returns a list containing object as defined below

| Key               | Datatype | Mandatory | Constraints                                                 |
| ----------------- | -------- | --------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
| id | String | Yes | |
| name              | String   | Yes       |                                                             |
| number            | String   | No        | Must be a valid ACN                                         |
| incorporationDate | String   | No        | ISO 8601 date https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601        |
| annualReviewDate  | String   | No        | ISO 8601 date https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601        |
| registrationState | String   | No        | Must be one of 'ACT'/'NSW'/'VIC'/'QLD'/'SA'/'WA'/'TAS'/'NT' |
| jurisdiction | String | Yes | Currently only 'Australia' is allowed |
| type              | Object   | No        | See table below                                             |
| agentId            | Number   | No        |                                             |
| registered            | boolean   | Yes        | false companies will show up in company registrations                                            |



**type object**

Note: Within Australia, only certain combinations of companyType, companyClass and companySubClass are valid

| Key             | Datatype | Mandatory | Constraints                                                                                                                                                    |
| --------------- | -------- | --------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| companyType     | String   | Yes       | Must be one of 'Small Proprietary'/'Large Proprietary'/'Public Company'                                                                                        |
| companyClass    | String   | Yes       | Must be one of 'Limited by Shares'/'Limited by Guarantee'/'Limited by Shares and Guarantee'/'Unlimited'/'No Liability'                                         |
| companySubClass | String   | Yes       | Must be one of 'None'/'Superannuation Trustee Company'/'Non Profit Company'/'Home Unit Company'/'Listed'/'Unlisted'/'Section 150 License'/'Unlisted Non Profit |

**details object** (Optional Paramter)


| Key             | Datatype | Mandatory | Constraints                                                                                                                                                    |
| --------------- | -------- | --------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| asicAgentNumber            | String   | No        | |
| annualReviewStatus    | String   | Yes       |                                         |
| annualReviewStatusDate | String   | No        | ISO 8601 date https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601 |
| labels    | String[]   | No       | Name of labels associated with the company  


**Additional keys**

| Key    | Datatype | Mandatory | Constraints |
| ------ | -------- | --------- | ----------- |
| offset | Number   | Yes       |             |
| limit  | Number   | Yes       |             |
| total  | Number   | Yes       |             |

request.description:
Steps to create a new company in CAS 360. 

1. [Create new company](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#2c3acc97-803f-4fb8-8ebd-32296c55bf8e). This will create the basic details for the company and return a companyId which can be used for adding further details. 
2. [Create Address](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#c2a5a9b1-4f78-474a-8344-50c79a10e655). Creates an address in CAS 360 and returns an addressId. If the address already exists, the existing addressId will be returned.
3. [Create Company Address](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#cca407dd-d840-4782-b837-7251cfd96062). Attach a new address to a CompanyId using adn AddressId. This includes Registered Office,  Address, Business Address, Postal Address or Meeting Address. 
4. [Create Contact](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#f36561e5-8286-458e-bf06-05e9411a004e). Creates a contact (officer, member, beneficial owner) in CAS 360 and returns a ContactId. If such contact already exists, the existing contactId will be returned without being modified.
5. [Create Company Officer](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#365630b5-5da2-43f9-acb6-87280f981d7a). Create a company officer (Director or Secretary) using a ContactId. 
6. [Create new share transaction](https://docs.api.bgl360.com.au/?version=latest#6587aad4-0fe7-4bdb-9754-6afa40e6f113). Create new share transaction for a given company. 

### Request Body

| Key               | Datatype | Mandatory | Constraints                                                 |
| ----------------- | -------- | --------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
| name              | String   | Yes       |                                                             |
| number            | String   | No        | Must be a valid ACN if jurisdiction is 'Australia'                         |
| incorporationDate | String   | No        | ISO 8601 date https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601        |
| annualReviewDate  | String   | No        | ISO 8601 date https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601        |
| registrationState | String   | No        | Must be one of 'ACT'/'NSW'/'VIC'/'QLD'/'SA'/'WA'/'TAS'/'NT' |
| jurisdiction | String | Yes | Currently only 'Australia' is allowed |
| type              | Object   | No        | See table below                                             |
| agentId              | String   | No        |                                              |
| registered              | boolean   | No        | False will be an unregistered company, if not specified will default to true                                             |


**type object**

Note: Within Australia, only certain combinations of companyType, companyClass and companySubClass are valid

| Key             | Datatype | Mandatory | Constraints                                                                                                                                                    |
| --------------- | -------- | --------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| companyType     | String   | Yes       | Must be one of 'Small Proprietary'/'Large Proprietary'/'Public Company'                                                                                        |
| companyClass    | String   | Yes       | Must be one of 'Limited by Shares'/'Limited by Guarantee'/'Limited by Shares and Guarantee'/'Unlimited'/'No Liability'                                         |
| companySubClass | String   | Yes       | Must be one of 'None'/'Superannuation Trustee Company'/'Non Profit Company'/'Home Unit Company'/'Listed'/'Unlisted'/'Section 150 License'/'Unlisted Non Profit |

When documents are generated, the status will automatically be set to Document Prepared. Once a document is lodged, the status will automatically change to Lodged. | id     | number     | Unique identifier   |

item.name: Webhooks

request.description:
## Encryption
 BGL will compute a Hash-based(SHA256) message authentication code (HMAC) using a secret key to protect the integrity and the authenticity of the message. The following logic will be used to generate a token which sends as an authorization header which can be decoded from provider's end with the same private key

    Authorization : "{clientCode} {UTC Date String} {Signature}"
    
           client code = this is code in lowercase unique for the client
           UTC Date String = timestamp in UTC format yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.sss'Z'
           Signature = This will contain following data which will generate HMAC using SHA256 hash, using configured secret. 
                               "{UTC Date String}POST{URI String}{RequestBody}"
    
          Calculating Signature,
    
          Signature = Base64Encoded(HMAC("{UTC Date String}POST{URI String}{RequestBody}"))

 
    

   ### Request Body

| Key| Mandatory| Type |Description |
| -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |
| userId     | Yes     | String | The email address of the user who has triggered the webhook     |
| firmId     | Yes     | String |  The Short Name or Firm ID of the firm     |
| entityId     | Yes     | String |  The ID of the resource that has changed. This could be with a companyId, trustId or fundId     |
| eventId     | Yes     | String | The Unique Identifier of the event provided by Simple Fund 360 or CAS 360     |
| eventType     | Yes     | String | The type of event of that occurred. This will be one of the following (constitution \ audit \ newsmsf)     |
| tenants | No | Array | see below |

**Tenants Array**

| Key| Mandatory| Type |Description |
| -------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |
| tenantId     | No     | String |  If applicable , the ID of the tenant that the event happened in relation to (e.g. ContactId or MemberId, Financial Year)     |
| tenantType     | No     | String | The type of tenant (contact \ member \ financialYear     |

   ### Responses 

Outlined below and in the examples are what BGL expects for webhook responses. 

-   Success
    
    -   response code: 200
        
    -   response type: application/json
        
    -   response body
        `{ message: "reqeust accepted." }`

-  Validation Error
    
    -   response code: 400
        
    -   response type: application/json
        
    -   response body
        `{ message: "missing required parameters", errors: [ "fundId is missing", "financialYear is missing" ] }`

-   Other Runtime Errors
    
    -   response code: 500
        
    -   response type: application/json
        
    -   response body
        `{ message: "System maintenance." }`

response.name: 400 - Error Reponse

request.description:
Allows a third-party to create a new contact into BGL Products (CAS 360 and/or Simple Fund 360)

### Path Variables
| Parameter              | Mandatory        | Datatype | Maximum Size | Description/Comments  |
|--------------------|------------------|--------|--------|-----------------------|
| firmId  | Yes              | String | 255 | The unique identifier of a firm in the external partner application                    |

### Request Body

| Field              | Mandatory        | Datatype | Maximum Size | Description/Comments  |
|--------------------|------------------|--------|--------|-----------------------|
| externalIdentifier | Yes              | String | 45 | Unique identifier of a contact in a firm of an external partner                       |
| firstName          | Yes/No*               | String | 255 | First name of the contact. For Individual entity type, this is mandatory field.                      |
| lastName           | Yes/No*               | String |255 |Last name of the contact. For Individual entity type, this is mandatory field.                       |
| name               | Yes/No*| String | 1000 | For Company, Trust, Partnership and SMSF entity types, this is mandatory.                      |
| email              | No               | String |255 |Email address of the contact                       |
| title              | No               | String |45 |Title of the contact                       |
| phone              | No               | String |255 | Phone number of the contact                       |
| mobile             | No               | String |45 | Mobile number of the contact                       |
| address            | Yes              | Object |N/A |Address of the contact. See object details in AddressObject table below.|
| businessStructure  | Yes              | String |45 |Business structure of the contact.                       |
| abn                | Yes/No*               | String |45 |Australian Business Number of the contact. For SMSF entity type, this is mandatory                       |
| acn                | Yes/No*                | String |45 |Australian Company Number of the contact. For Company entity type, this is mandatory field.                       |
| dateOfBirth        | No               | Date |N/A |Date of Birth of the contact. Format: yyyy-mm-dd                       |

*indicates may be mandatory depending on other data



###  Address Object
| Field              | Mandatory        | Datatype | Maximum Size | Description/Comments  |
|--------------------|------------------|--------|--------|-----------------------|
| postalCode | Yes              | String | 45 | Postal code of the address   |
| addressLine1 | Yes              | String | 50 | First line of the address   |
| addressLine2 | Yes              | String | 255 | Second line of the address   |
| city | Yes              | String | 45 | City/Town of the address   |
| region | Yes              | String | 45 | State of the address   |
| country | Yes              | String | 45 | Country of the address   |
